title: Sing It Loud - Songs of Protest
description:
SING IT LOUD- Songs of Protest 
A live concert event.
(NPS Upper Delaware National Scenic and Recreation Area and Narrowsburg, NY)

Singer songwriters from a small rural community in upstate NY and surrounding areas will be performing SING IT LOUD, a live concert featuring songs of protest intended to inspire people locally and nationally to do the same on street corners, in clubs and concert halls, online and everywhere music can be heard. The producers are declaring Sunday May 18, 2025 ‚ÄúNATIONAL SING IT LOUD DAY.‚Äù 

The concert will be presented Sunday, May 18, 2025 from 1 - 3 PM before a live audience in Delaware Hall at The Narrowsburg Union, 7 Erie Avenue, Narrowsburg, NY 12764.  

Admission is free but contributions will be gladly accepted. 

 The event will be streamed live on Facebook. The program features classic and original protest songs and includes a sing-along with the audience.

   SING IT LOUD is being produced by Kathy Joan Geary, Cynthia Nash and Jill Padua and was first conceived by Jane Bollinger after reading a January 2025 Rolling Stone article ‚ÄúThe 100 Best Protest Songs of All Time‚Äù.

   Says Kathy Geary, host of ‚ÄúNow and Then‚Äù on WJFF and a prominent member of the music scene in the region, ‚ÄúThe music of protest has a long history in the United States of America, and its songs are a testament to defining moments in the history of this nation.‚Äù

   Cynthia Nash adds ‚ÄúThis concert of songs of protest gives voice to our differences, even as we seek a ‚Äúmore perfect‚Äù union.  It is a celebration of free speech through song.‚Äù

   For further information about this concert and the SING IT LOUD movement please go to our website at https://Sing-It-Loud.com and visit our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/singitloud.concerts.

title: Indivisible Red & Rural Caucus May Call
description:
What does Pride mean to you? What do you think it means and looks like for your small or rural community? 

Now take what you said, and think about it from a different angle. What does Pride mean to the LGBTQIA+ community who lives in red, rural or small town America? Right now, Pride is one of the last bastions of all positive visibility for people who identify as LGBTQIA+, and more than ever before this pride is under attack. 

From the Trump administration on day one stating that there are only two sexes and genders, to the right wing attacks against all Transgender individuals (children and adults alike), people in our communities are scared. They feel as though attacks come from every side today and they feel as though their community is at risk. 

Here at the Indivisible Red and Rural Caucus, we know how tough it is to live in red, rural and small town America, and now that we have all defined what community means to us, it's our job to be inclusive and supportive of all communities. June is Pride Month, and we are ready to turn out to support all individuals regardless of whether they are Gay, Lesbian, Transgender, Questioning, Intersex, Asexual and beyond! Join us for our May Red and Rural Caucus where we will learn how to continue rebuilding our communities in small town America by supporting one of the most at risk communities there is in our nation. When we stand together in community and collectively raise our voices, its much harder for fascists to fight us. 

Join us on May 28th for a Pride Themed Red and Rural Caucus Call, and learn how you can be the best Ally all year round, not just during Pride!

This meeting will also have a virtual option to accommodate accessibility needs! Register for the link.

title: How Can Ranked Choice Voting Elect Progressive Champions This Primary Election?
description:
NYC elections use Ranked Choice Voting as of 2021- but what the heck is Ranked Choice Voting?!

Join Citizen Action members for a training on Ranked Choice Voting led by Citizen Action's in-house expert, Democracy Coordinator Karen Wharton, so we can all be informed and ready to vote ahead of the NYC Democratic Primary election on June 24th, 2025, where voters will choose their next city council member, Comptroller, District Attorney, Borough President, and Mayor!

Ranked choice voting can be a powerful tool for electing progressive candidates if used correctly, and allows voters to support their top choice candidate without having to worry about "throwing away their vote" by not voting for the frontrunners. 

Join us for our next training- you wont want to miss it!
